This project implements a user interface system where a trimpot (analog input device) is used to navigate and select different operational modes displayed on an OLED screen. The trimpot value is read through the ADC of the microcontroller and mapped to discrete menu options such as Mode 1, Mode 2, and Mode 3. The selected mode is highlighted on the OLED, enabling smooth and intuitive analog-based navigation without buttons.

The system demonstrates real-time analog signal processing, user interface design, and mode-based control logic. It can be extended for applications like smart controllers, device configuration systems, and embedded dashboards where quick and flexible user interaction is required.
